steps.instruction:
### Making The Starter
- Mix 1 cup of lukewarm water, 1/2 teaspoon of any kind of yeast, 1.25 cups of bread flour, and 1/4 cup of whole wheat flour
- Cover with plastic wrap
- Let rest for at *least* 2 hours and no more than 16 hours

### Making The Dough
- Combine the starter with 1 cup of lukewarm water, 3/4 teaspoon of active dry yeast, 1 tablespoon of sugar, 3.25 of bread flour (the rest of the dough flour will be added later), and 1.75 teaspoons of salt
- Stir to combine
- Let rest for 12 to 15 minutes
- Sir again
- Knead the dough and add the additional 3/4 of a cup of bread flour
- Make sure the new flour is all combined in
- Let rest for 10 to 12 minutes

### Let Rest
- Place the dough in a lightly greased bowl and cover with greased plastic wrap
- Let rise until the dough has doubled in volume (around 1 to 2 hours)

### Shaping
- Deflate the dough gently, but don't get rid of all of the air
- Form the dough into a round ball
- Place cornmeal or semolina dusted sheet of parchment paper onto a baking sheet
- Put the ball of dough onto the sheets, seem side down
- Cover the dough with greased plastic wrap
- Let sit for 45 to 90 minutes

### Baking
- Preheat the oven for 475F
- Slash or -cross-hatch the bread with a sharp knife
- Dust with a little flour
- Spray a little water into the oven with a spray bottle
- Put the bread into the oven
- Reduce temperature to 425F
- Bake for 25 to 30 minutes
    - Spray water into the oven every few minutes for at least the first 15 minutes of baking
